# My Values

These are the ideas that guide the way I work, learn, and collaborate.

---

## 🧩 Systems Thinking  
Whether mechanical, organizational, or digital, I’m drawn to understanding how things fit together. Most problems aren’t “one thing” — they’re interactions between many things. I like solving those.

---

## 🛠️ Craftsmanship  
I believe in building things that last: clean processes, reliable automations, accurate data, and thoughtful workflows. Good systems make work easier for everyone.

---

## 🔍 Clarity  
Ambiguity creates waste. I value transparency, clear communication, and shared understanding — the foundations of any healthy team or project.

---

## 🌱 Continuous Learning  
Returning to college later in life taught me the value of curiosity and adaptability. Today that shows up through PMP studies, Python, SEO/AI experimentation, and a general desire to keep improving.

---

## 🚲 Service  
I volunteer as a mechanic and instructor at Community Cycles because access to transportation changes lives. Teaching and supporting others has become an important part of who I am.

---

## 🤝 Kindness & Integrity  
I try to approach people with empathy, humility, and honesty. The best work happens when people feel safe to collaborate, experiment, and speak candidly.

---
